          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Question regarding force-carbing. I decided to throw together a seltzer setup for the gf while I wait for the next batch to be ready, and I've noticed the tank pressure gauge has dropped tremendously since I put the CO2 tank into the fridge. High-school chemistry tells me that it's supposed to happen, <strike>and the math works out</strike> (units, gdi! the math is actually way off I think) so this is mostly just for peace-of-mind than anything else, but is it normal for that to happen? Dropped from about 600 psi at room temp to about 400 at 35F<br /><br />Also, how do I tell if there's a leak besides the obvious hissing?

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
