        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              The pressure reading is normal.  Essentially, the high-pressure gauge on the regulator is just a thermometer labeled in PSI.  <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/razz.png" alt=":p" title="Razz" />  I actually removed the high-pressure gauges from my regulators since they are nearly completely useless - the only way to really know how much is left is to weigh the tank.<br /><br />To locate leaks, you can spray all the fittings with star-san, or soapy water as is commonly used to test household gas plumbing.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
