          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              I soaked them in a PBW mixture in the sink ... around 20 minutes, and the labels peeled off fine .. I just had to wash off the glue gunk with a dish cloth .. but other than that it wasn't bad.  Lesson learned though, I do need a bottle tree.  Badly.  <br /><br />I threw together a real quick and cheap American Amber Ale yesterday, and the airlock is chugging away right now.. it's a lovely sight.  But reality is that I'll have to bottle this beast in another week and change .. and I'm going to have to buy 2 cases of bottles .. no way I'll drink that much commercial beer by then!

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
