              I have an American Amber Ale in primary that I'm going to try to bottle this weekend.. I was thinking about adding some blueberry flavor to it via one of those little 4oz bottles the LHBS sells.  Had I thought about it I'd have racked it to secondary over some fruit but ... ain't nobody got time fo dat.  Anyone have any experience with the 4oz bottles of fruit flavor?  One came with my Chocolate Raspberry Stout (raspberry, d'uh) .. I just tried that beer and I'm not getting much raspberry.  I want the blueberry to be there but not overpowering like the Sam Adams Cherry wheat cherry.  1 bottle or 2 for 5 gallons?

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
