          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle"><a href="http://arstechnica.com/civis/viewtopic.php?p=24414609#p24414609" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">Pysgard</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">For year long, you want to avoid Plastic, from my understanding. It's ever so slightly permeable to oxygen, which is enemy of flavor.</div><br /><br />Oak is slightly permeable to oxygen too. One brewing book I've read suggested you need some oxygen entering for proper flavor development. It was specifically regarding aging sour beers and slow-acting wild yeasts but could apply anywhere you're trying to simulate barrel aging. Their solution wasn't plastic though; they suggested cutting a piece of oak into the shape of a carboy bung.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
